Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Spray 8- or 9-inch square baking pan with no-stick cooking spray. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and allspice. Add melted butter, egg and milk. Mix vigorously until well blended. Pour half of batter into greased and floured pan; spread SMUCKER'S(R) preserves evenly over batter. Top with remaining batter. Combine topping ingredients; mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over top of coffee cake. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.